subject: Hockey, Field
lead_paragraph: Eastern High School’s nine-year dynasty in New Jersey field hockey is over. The Vikings’ 208-game unbeaten streak against state rivals ended Wednesday night in a 3-2 overtime loss to Oak Knoll of Summit in the semifinals of the state tournament of champions. Eastern, in Voorhees, won nine consecutive state Group 4 titles and posted a 204-0-4 mark against New Jersey schools in a run that began at the start of the 1999 season. The school’s last loss was a 2-1 decision to Shawnee on Nov. 13, 1998, in the South Jersey Group 4 title game.
